  "Minimal API 是什么": "What Minimal API is",
  "传统 ASP.NET Core 要你建 Controller 类、写特性标注。Minimal API 把这一切压缩到一个文件里：构建器造出 app，然后直接挂路由。它适合小服务、原型和微服务，启动代码少、心智负担低。整个程序就是一段顶层语句，没有 Main 方法的样板。": "Classic ASP.NET Core makes you create Controller classes with attributes. Minimal API collapses all of that into one file: a builder creates app, then you attach routes directly. It suits small services, prototypes and microservices, with little startup code and low mental overhead. The whole program is top-level statements with no Main boilerplate.",
  "三步走：Builder、Map、Run": "Three steps: Builder, Map, Run",
  "第一步 CreateBuilder(args) 读取配置、命令行参数；第二步 Build() 得到 WebApplication 实例 app；第三步在 app 上挂路由，最后 app.Run() 启动监听。MapGet 的第二个参数是一个委托——通常是 lambda，框架在请求到来时调用它。": "Step one: CreateBuilder(args) reads config and command-line args. Step two: Build() returns the WebApplication instance app. Step three: attach routes on app, then app.Run() starts listening. The second argument of MapGet is a delegate, usually a lambda the framework invokes when a request arrives.",
  "一个完整可运行的 Minimal API": "A complete runnable Minimal API",
  "返回字符串时框架默认用 text/plain，不会加引号——和返回对象的 JSON 行为不同。": "Returning a string defaults to text/plain with no quotes, unlike returning an object which becomes JSON.",
  "别把 Run 写在前面": "Don't put Run first",
  "app.Run() 是阻塞调用，它一旦执行就进入监听循环。所有 MapGet/MapPost 必须写在 app.Run() 之前，否则路由还没注册服务就跑起来了，请求会得到 404。": "app.Run() is a blocking call; once it executes it enters the listening loop. Every MapGet/MapPost must come before app.Run(), otherwise the server starts before routes are registered and requests get 404.",
  "Run() 之后的注册代码不会生效，记得把路由全部放在它上面。": "Registration code after Run() has no effect; keep all routes above it.",
